{{Quote|She'll be all right. Inform Lord Vader we have a prisoner.|DV-692, referring to Leia Organa|<ref name="ANH" />}}
'''DV-692''' was a [[clone stormtrooper]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] who served in the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], he was stationed aboard the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Devastator/Legends|''Devastator'']] under the command of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]]. DV-692 participated in the ''Devastator''{{'s}} [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|capture]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]] [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']] and led a [[Unidentified stormtrooper squad|squad]] in searching for the passengers of the [[Starship/Legends|ship]]. In one of the [[Corvette/Legends|corvette's]] passageways, the [[Squad/Legends|squad]] spotted the [[Alderaanian/Legends|Alderaanian]] [[Senator/Legends|senator]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], and DV-692 [[Stun/Legends|stunned]] her as she tried to escape. His unit escorted their [[Prisoner/Legends|captive]] to Vader and then to the ''Devastator''{{'s}} [[Prison/Legends|prison]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|Search that passageway and secure the junction. Hold all Rebel prisoners for collection. The rest of you stick with me.|DV-692, to his squad|<ref name="radio">[[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'' radio drama]]</ref>}}
[[File:Stun1.png|thumb|left|250px|DV-692, firing on Organa]]
DV-692<ref name="tcg" /> was a [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="CVD" /> [[Gender/Legends|male]]<ref name="SE" /> [[Cloning/Legends|clone]]<ref name="tcg" /> who served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]<ref name="ANH" /> as a lower [[Officer/Legends|officer]]<ref name="ANH novel">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref> in the [[Stormtrooper Corps/Legends|Stormtrooper Corps]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. He was a member of the elite [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Legion/Legends|legion]] known as the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st]],<ref name="TCSWE" /> and was assigned to lead a [[Unidentified stormtrooper squad|squad]] within the legion.<ref name="anh-junior">[[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope (junior novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' junior novelization]]</ref> In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> DV-692 was stationed aboard the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Devastator/Legends|''Devastator'']], [[Commanding officer/Legends|commanded]] by the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]].<ref name="anh-junior" />

That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] agents transmitted the stolen [[Death Star plans/Legends|plans]] of the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]], a new Imperial [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]], to the Rebel [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]] [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']]. Over the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], the ''Devastator'' pursued and [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|captured]] the ''Tantive IV'', which was the [[Consular ship/Legends|consular ship]] of [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] of the planet [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]. Led by an [[Unidentified stormtrooper commander (Tantive IV)|assault commander]],<ref name="ANH" /> DV-692 and his [[Squad/Legends|squad]] boarded the ''Tantive IV'' as part of the first wave of stormtroopers. After the Imperial [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]] cleared out the initial Rebel resistance, Vader came aboard the [[Starship/Legends|ship]] and ordered the stormtroopers to search for the passengers of the ''Tantive IV'' and capture them alive.<ref name="radio" />

DV-692 split the troopers of his squad into two groups; he ordered half of them to search a passageway and secure a junction and led the rest to another corridor. The squad's orders were to search the passageways astern and forward.<ref name="radio" /> One of DV-692's [[Unidentified 501st stormtrooper|squadmates]] spotted Organa hiding in a small alcove and alerted DV-692 of her presence; however, Organa outdrew DV-692's squadmate and shot him [[Death/Legends|dead]]. Organa then tried to escape, but DV-692 [[Stun/Legends|stunned]] her with his [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]]. The squad escorted Organa to Vader, who ordered them to take the [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] to the ''Devastator''{{'s}} [[Prison/Legends|holding facility]].<ref name="ANH" />

==Equipment==
DV-692 wore full [[Stormtrooper armor/Legends|stormtrooper armor]] without [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] insignia and used an E-11 stormtrooper [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifle]] during the battle aboard the ''Tantive IV''.<ref name="ANH" />

==Behind the scenes==
===''A New Hope'' and early character development===
{{Quote|Report to Lord Vader.|DV-692's line from the ''A New Hope'' novel|<ref name="ANH novel" />}}
[[File:Dv-692.jpg|thumb|right|300px|DV-692, inspecting Organa in [[Dark Horse Comics]]'s [[Star Wars: A New Hope - The Special Edition 1|adaptation of ''A New Hope'']]]]
The character of DV-692 first appeared in the [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|novelization]] of [[George Lucas]]'s [[1977]] film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']],<ref name="ANH novel" /> published on [[November 12]], [[1976]] and ghost-written by [[Alan Dean Foster]].<ref name="ANH novel SE">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]] {{C|[[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Edition]] foreword by [[George Lucas]]}}</ref> In the novel, DV-692 wore rank insignia on his arm,<ref name="ANH novel" /> but he did not have any such insignia in the film<ref name="ANH" /> which was released on [[May 25]], 1977.<ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> His first visual appearance was in the [[Star Wars (1977) 1|first issue]] of [[Marvel Comics]]'s [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'' series]],<ref name="marvel">[[Star Wars (1977) 1|''Star Wars'' (1977) 1]]</ref> published on [[April 12]], 1977,<ref name="Marvel April">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/53791/star_wars_1977_1|text=Star Wars (1977) #1}} {{C|First printing}}</ref> written by [[Roy Thomas]], and illustrated by [[Howard Chaykin]], [[Jim Novak]], and [[Marie Severin]]. Notably, only his right [[Limb/Legends|hand]] and feet were pictured in the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]].<ref name="marvel" />

His first live-action appearance occurred in the film ''A New Hope'' itself, in which he was portrayed by an uncredited extra.<ref name="ANH" /> The scene was one of the last few of principle photography in the [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]] and was filmed sometime between [[June 29]] and [[July 16]], 1976,<ref name="making-definitive">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> in [[Elstree Studios]].<ref name="Aficionado">{{Blogspot|subdomain=starwarsaficionado|url=2015/05/behind-scenes-blockade-runner-battlers.html|name=Star Wars Aficionado|text=BEHIND THE SCENES: BLOCKADE RUNNER BATTLERS|date=2015-05-10}}</ref> DV-692's lines, performed by [[Wikipedia:Disc jockey|disc jockey]] [[Terence McGovern|Terry McGovern]], were said over a walkie-talkie and recorded by sound designer [[Ben Burtt]]. The sound effect of his stun shot was a mix of an [[Wikipedia:ARP Instruments|ARP]] synthesizer playing a note with a "rising pitch and a delay" to bombinate combined with the sound of an air cannon.<ref name="sound">''[[The Sounds of Star Wars]]''</ref> DV-692's helmet was missing a heat dispenser vent decal, which should have been located on the helmet's "cheeks."<ref name="vg">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/explore/visualguides/chp04.html|text=Episode IV Visual Guide &mdash; Chapter 4: Artoo's Mission}}</ref> In [[2002]], the [[A New Hope (TCG)|''A New Hope'']] expansion set of [[Wizards of the Coast]]'s ''[[Star Wars Trading Card Game]]'' was the first to identify the trooper as "DV-692," a clone stormtrooper.<ref name="tcg" />

===Inconsistencies===
{{Quote|Watch it! She's armed! Fire! &hellip; Good shooting. She'll be all right. Inform Lord Vader that we have a prisoner.|DV-692's expanded line from the radio drama|<ref name="radio" />}}
[[File:Trooper-shot-by-Leia-ANH.jpg|thumb|right|230px|In ''Classic Star Wars: A New Hope'', DV-692's role is combined with that of his squadmate (pictured).]]
The script of the [[1981]] [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'' radio drama]], as presented in [[1994]]'s ''[[Star Wars: The National Public Radio Dramatization]]'', addressed DV-692 as "3rd Trooper."<ref name="radioscript">[[Star Wars: The National Public Radio Dramatization|''Star Wars'': The National Public Radio Dramatization]]</ref> His line in the radio drama was a bit longer and suggested that he did not shoot Organa but that another trooper from his squad fired on her.<ref name="radio" />

DV-692's dialogue varies slightly from the various adaptations of the film, including the novelization,<ref name="ANH novel" /> the radio drama,<ref name="radio" /> the Marvel comic,<ref name="marvel" /> and the comic ''[[Contemporary Motivators: Star Wars]]'' published in 1977.<ref name="motivators">''[[Contemporary Motivators: Star Wars]]''</ref> Additionally, in the [[1995]] [[Classic Star Wars: A New Hope (Random House)|''Classic Star Wars: A New Hope'']] adaptation, the role of DV-692 and his companion shot by Organa is merged into that of a stormtrooper [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]], who calls out Leia's presence and stuns her, though not before she manages to shoot two other stormtroopers.<ref name="Classic SW">[[Classic Star Wars: A New Hope (Random House)|''Classic Star Wars: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref>

